09:51.757 --> 09:53.025 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What are they looking for there?

09:53.059 --> 09:54.694 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: I don't think you are
going to
see a lot of details.

09:54.727 --> 09:56.495 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's funny.

09:56.529 --> 09:59.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president this, that he
would announce
his tax reform plan on this
Wednesday just

09:59.332 --> 10:03.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about -- maybe just minutes
after Treasury
Secretary Mnuchin said it wasn't
going to

10:03.869 --> 10:05.371 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
come for quite a while.

10:05.404 --> 10:08.841 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't think you're going to
see a lot of
details on Wednesday.

10:08.874 --> 10:15.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Secretary Mnuchin, the National
Economic Council
chairman, Gary Cohn, are going
to the Hill

10:15.214 --> 10:20.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
tomorrow to talk to Speaker
Ryan, Leader McConnell,
the leaders of the tax-writing
committees.

10:20.386 --> 10:26.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On Wednesday, the most you could
see is, I
think, probably guidelines,
broad principles,

10:26.559 --> 10:33.132 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
middle-class tax cut,
simplification of the
tax code, making business rates
competitive,

10:33.165 --> 10:35.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
which means cutting them, but
probably not
much more than that.

10:35.635 --> 10:38.270 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Lisa, what
are folks on
the Hill saying about this?

10:38.304 --> 10:41.140 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: I was standing
next to Finance
Chairman Orrin Hatch, who has
been talking

10:41.173 --> 10:44.176 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the White House about tax
reform for a
long time.

10:44.210 --> 10:46.445 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he actually received a call
from the White
House when I was standing there.

10:46.479 --> 10:49.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said he hasn't been briefed
on this plan
yet, on what they're going to
say tomorrow.

10:49.982 --> 10:51.617 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But he says what John is
reporting.

10:51.651 --> 10:53.419 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It will be vague.

10:53.452 --> 10:56.422 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We asked, there's reports about
a 15 percent
corporate tax rate, that the
president wants

10:56.455 --> 10:58.157 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to make that drastic cut.

10:58.190 --> 11:01.427 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
To that, Hatch said, "I don't
think he will
get away with that."

11:01.460 --> 11:03.262 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Essentially, that would be too
much of a budget
buster.

11:03.295 --> 11:07.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, that's kind of already from
a Trump supporter
a problem for him.

11:07.733 --> 11:10.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: This is somebody
they'd normally
be counting on.

11:10.136 --> 11:14.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, just quickly, less than a
minute, you
mentioned health care a minute
ago, John,

11:14.140 --> 11:17.643 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that the White House is ready to
deal on that.

11:17.677 --> 11:20.212 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Where are they in coming up with
a new health
care reform plan?

11:20.246 --> 11:23.182 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: They think that their
contribution
has been to get the conservative
Republicans

11:23.215 --> 11:25.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the moderate Republicans
talking to each
other.

11:25.351 --> 11:30.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They say the vote is up to the
Hill, up to
the speaker, the majority leader
and the whip

11:30.056 --> 11:31.791 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
once they have the votes.

11:31.824 --> 11:35.594 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They would love for it to happen
before the
100 days is up, but they also
realize that

11:35.628 --> 11:37.997 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
keeping the government opening
and running
takes precedence.

11:38.030 --> 11:39.532 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What do you hear?

11:39.565 --> 11:41.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Judy, I woke to
a wide spectrum
of offices on Capitol Hill.

11:41.267 --> 11:42.268 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They're not there yet.

11:42.301 --> 11:43.269 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Maybe tomorrow night.

11:43.302 --> 11:45.371 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Freedom Caucus has an
important meeting.

11:45.404 --> 11:47.440 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They say there's a little bit of
optimism
among Republicans.

11:47.473 --> 11:51.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But this whole year, Judy, they
have been
big on aspiration, short on
votes.

11:51.043 --> 11:52.978 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All right.

11:53.012 --> 11:56.849 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, I know both of you are
going to be following
it all this week, Lisa
Desjardins, John Yang.

11:56.882 --> 12:01.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, Lisa, stay with us, because
you mentioned
this West Virginia coal miners
issue several

12:02.021 --> 12:02.988 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
times.

12:03.022 --> 12:03.989 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And you have actually done
reporting.

12:04.023 --> 12:05.558 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You have been to West Virginia.

12:05.591 --> 12:06.559 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Tell us more.

12:06.592 --> 12:07.727 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: That's right.

12:07.760 --> 12:09.628 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We just got back from West
Virginia over the
weekend.

12:09.662 --> 12:14.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And President Trump, as you
know, has campaigned
on a promise to reverse the
fortunes of coal

12:14.100 --> 12:15.868 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
country.

12:15.901 --> 12:18.404 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
That message especially
resonated in West
Virginia, where he swept every
single county

12:18.437 --> 12:20.239 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in last year's elections.

12:20.272 --> 12:24.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But now thousands of miners are
in jeopardy
of losing their health care if
Congress doesn't

12:24.944 --> 12:26.846 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
act.

12:26.879 --> 12:29.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is another installment in
our ongoing
Chasing the Dream series on
poverty and opportunity

12:29.982 --> 12:32.785 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in America.

12:32.818 --> 12:38.390 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Many stories about mining start
here, a coal
yard in Appalachia.

12:38.424 --> 12:42.895 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But this story starts here in a
front yard.

12:42.928 --> 12:48.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After 27 years underground,
former miner Damon
Tucker left with a list of
health problems

12:48.200 --> 12:49.268 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and frustrations.

12:49.301 --> 12:51.237 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAMON TUCKER, Former Coal Miner:
I told my
wife.

12:51.270 --> 12:53.539 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I said, I will flip hamburgers.

12:53.572 --> 12:57.710 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I will draw my pension and flip
hamburgers
if I have to.

12:57.743 --> 13:00.346 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm not -- I'm coming out of the
mines.

13:00.379 --> 13:03.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Flipping
hamburgers didn't
happen.

13:03.182 --> 13:08.120 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lawn care did with his own
one-man business
near Beckley, West Virginia.

13:08.154 --> 13:13.659 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Tucker, who had open heart
surgery just
over a year ago, still depends
on his miners

13:13.692 --> 13:15.161 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
health plan.

13:15.194 --> 13:18.764 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So what would it mean if your
health care
benefits just stopped?

13:18.798 --> 13:23.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAMON TUCKER: Well, you know, I
will take
what medicine I can afford to
pay right now,

13:24.003 --> 13:30.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but my follow-up visits with
doctors and stuff,
I won't -- I won't go.

13:30.309 --> 13:33.679 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I -- you know, I won't be able
to afford to
go.

13:33.712 --> 13:39.552 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Some 22,000
retired union
miners and their widows will
lose their health

13:39.585 --> 13:41.687 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
care if Congress doesn't act.

13:41.720 --> 13:43.556 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Many have chronic lung diseases.

13:43.589 --> 13:48.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Their union benefit health plan
supports clinics
like this in Southern West
Virginia and helps

13:48.327 --> 13:49.795 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
them pay their medical costs.

13:49.829 --> 13:52.998 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WOMAN: Take a deep breath in.

13:53.032 --> 14:00.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: These retired
miners say
the federal government
guaranteed this health

14:00.139 --> 14:06.745 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
care at a key moment 70 years
ago, 1946.

14:06.779 --> 14:11.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After a massive miner strike
threatened the
power grid, President Truman did
something

14:11.183 --> 14:16.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
historic: He stepped in to forge
a deal where
coal companies and the mining
union agreed

14:16.522 --> 14:19.391 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to fund lifelong health care and
pensions.

14:19.425 --> 14:22.328 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: I blame the government more
than I do
the coal companies.

14:22.361 --> 14:26.398 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: That
last-century promise
is colliding with today's
funding problem

14:26.432 --> 14:30.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and critical health needs at a
meeting of
the Fayette County Black Lung
Association.

14:30.402 --> 14:35.307 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: They want to send me to a
lung doctor
the 1st of next month.

14:35.341 --> 14:41.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, if they don't pass that
bill, then the
1st of the next month, I won't
have no insurance.

14:41.213 --> 14:46.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: I would like to say my
breathing and
everything's getting better, but
it's not.

14:46.185 --> 14:47.853 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's getting worse.

14:47.887 --> 14:52.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: It'll take us going back to
Washington,
and protesting, and letting them
know how

14:52.691 --> 14:54.026 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
we feel.

14:54.059 --> 14:56.328 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We need to let the government
know: Hey, you
all promised that.

14:56.362 --> 14:57.463 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We supposed to get that.

14:57.496 --> 14:59.365 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: How did this
happen?

14:59.398 --> 15:04.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As the coal industry declined,
there were
fewer miners paying into the
system, and more

15:04.103 --> 15:07.206 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
miners retiring and drawing on
their benefits.

15:07.239 --> 15:12.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Starting in the 1990s, coal
companies used
bankruptcy filings as a way to
stop paying

15:12.177 --> 15:14.713 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
their portion of the benefits.

15:14.747 --> 15:20.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All that led to shortfalls, and
while government
never intended to pay for these
benefits,

15:20.085 --> 15:24.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Congress has become a kind of
funder of last
resort, and has stepped in
multiple times

15:24.990 --> 15:26.325 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to make up the difference.

15:26.358 --> 15:28.727 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that brings us to today.

15:28.761 --> 15:31.864 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Miners' fates are yet again in
the hands of
Washington politicians.

15:31.897 --> 15:37.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, notably, this time, miners'
health benefits
run out as another deadline
hits, the deadline

15:38.003 --> 15:39.571 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to fund most of government.

15:39.605 --> 15:41.407 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

15:41.440 --> 15:42.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOE MANCHIN (D), West Virginia:
How many in
here are depending on this
health care we're

15:42.574 --> 15:44.276 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
talking about?

15:44.310 --> 15:46.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: West Virginia
Democratic
Senator Joe Manchin, drawing
packed rooms

15:46.745 --> 15:51.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of miners at Southern West
Virginia Community
College, wants to solve their
health care

15:51.350 --> 15:55.721 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
issue permanently by leveraging
the overlapping
crises.

15:55.754 --> 15:59.591 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He doesn't use the word
shutdown, but his
moves could lead to one.

15:59.625 --> 16:04.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says he and other Democrats
could block
or delay government funding this
week.

16:04.263 --> 16:08.734 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is the only way that you could
support the
next funding bill if it contains
a permanent

16:08.767 --> 16:09.835 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
fix for these health care
benefits?

16:09.868 --> 16:11.103 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

16:11.136 --> 16:12.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOE MANCHIN: As of I'm speaking
of you right
now, absolutely.

16:12.838 --> 16:17.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's what I'm fighting for, and
it's what's
basically the only right thing
to do.

16:17.076 --> 16:22.481 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But West
Virginia Republican
Congressman David McKinley says,
for now,

16:22.514 --> 16:28.320 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
he's OK with less, a
20-month-or-so patch
that would mean another fix
needed after the

16:28.354 --> 16:29.321 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
2018 election.

16:29.355 --> 16:31.056 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

16:31.090 --> 16:32.458 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DAVID MCKINLEY (R), West
Virginia: Look, I
would embrace what he's talking
about over

16:32.491 --> 16:35.694 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on the Senate side, but you
don't shut government
down over this.

16:35.728 --> 16:38.430 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Let's be reasonable about it,
and not give
false hope.

16:38.464 --> 16:42.901 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Another
potential divide,
McKinley is considering running
against Manchin

16:42.935 --> 16:45.170 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for Senate next year.

16:45.204 --> 16:50.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still others look at coal
country, despite
Truman's involvement, and say
it's time Congress

16:50.509 --> 16:52.411 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to stop funding these benefits.

16:52.444 --> 16:55.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL GRESZLER, Heritage
Foundation: That
promise came from their
employees and the

16:55.748 --> 16:56.715 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
union.

16:56.749 --> 16:58.384 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It didn't come from the
government.

16:58.417 --> 17:00.452 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Rachel Greszler
from the
conservative Heritage Foundation
points out

17:00.486 --> 17:04.056 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
miners are far from the only
group facing
benefit problems.

17:04.089 --> 17:07.659 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RACHEL GRESZLER: If the
government steps in
now and says, just because you
performed a

17:07.693 --> 17:12.564 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
very valuable service, and coal
mining is
crucial to our country, we're
going to bail

17:12.598 --> 17:18.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you out, what does that say to
any other worker
who sees their job as very
valuable, and yet

17:18.337 --> 17:22.007 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their union and their employers
can't make
good on the promises they
provided?

17:22.041 --> 17:26.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KATHY VANCE, Widow: It doesn't
even look like
he had started to develop black
lung at that

17:26.979 --> 17:28.847 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
point.

17:28.881 --> 17:31.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But Kathy
Vance, whose husband,
Larry, died of complications
from black lung,

17:31.283 --> 17:35.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
says miners are different
because the federal
government was involved in their
benefits

17:35.220 --> 17:37.089 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from the beginning.

17:37.122 --> 17:41.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She's a cancer survivor herself
and her widow's
benefits help with doctors
visits and medicine.

17:41.293 --> 17:47.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KATHY VANCE: It's just, you
know, a constant
worry of, are we going to have
health benefits

17:47.066 --> 17:48.801 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
or not?

17:48.834 --> 17:54.273 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He would be very angry, because,
you know,
he -- he supported the union
wholeheartedly.

17:54.306 --> 18:00.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: This crisis
over miners benefits
comes under one of the most
pro-coal-sounding

18:00.045 --> 18:01.847 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
presidents in decades.

18:01.880 --> 18:05.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
And in other countries, they
love their coal.

18:05.150 --> 18:08.087 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Over here, we haven't treated it
with the
respect it deserves.

18:08.120 --> 18:12.624 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But President
Trump has been
publicly silent on miners
benefits.

18:12.658 --> 18:13.826 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And Manchin wants more.

18:13.859 --> 18:15.627 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

18:15.661 --> 18:17.896 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOE MANCHIN: I'm very appreciate
President
Trump's willingness to want to
help the coal

18:17.930 --> 18:18.897 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
miners.

18:18.931 --> 18:20.732 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We just need him now to step
forward.

18:20.766 --> 18:24.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Back outside
