20:04.369 --> 20:08.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Robert Laszewski is a consultant
who works
with health insurers and other
industry leaders.

20:08.974 --> 20:10.742 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He watches this issue closely.

20:10.776 --> 20:13.111 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Robert Laszewski, thank you for
being back
with us.

20:13.145 --> 20:15.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT LASZEWSKI, President,
Health Care Policy
and Marketplace Review: You're
welcome.

20:15.447 --> 20:19.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, remind us,
325 million
Americans, only seven million of
them receive

20:19.751 --> 20:20.719 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
these subsidies.

20:20.752 --> 20:21.720 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ROBERT LASZEWSKI: Yes.

20:21.753 --> 20:23.555 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Why does this
matter so much?

20:23.589 --> 20:25.390 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT LASZEWSKI: Well, first of
all, there
are 20 million people in the
individual health

20:25.424 --> 20:29.194 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
insurance market, so it does
affect 20 million
people.

20:29.228 --> 20:33.732 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the subsidies, the Trump
administration
can cut them off tomorrow
morning.

20:33.765 --> 20:38.070 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
To the typical insurance
company, that could
be worth about $8 million a
month they'd lose,

20:38.103 --> 20:40.872 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
because they still have to
provide the benefits.

20:40.906 --> 20:44.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So what the insurance company
does, if this
gets cut off overnight, is that
they will

20:45.010 --> 20:49.581 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
