just for the
seven million in the exchange,
but the 20

20:49.615 --> 20:51.817 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
million in the individual health
insurance
market.

20:51.850 --> 20:56.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that could easily lead to 15
percent rate
increases on top of significant
rate increases

20:56.989 --> 20:59.124 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that are likely to come in 2018
for Obamacare.

20:59.157 --> 21:01.293 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Let's try to
humanize this.

21:01.326 --> 21:03.829 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Who exactly are the people who
benefit from
this?

21:03.862 --> 21:07.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT LASZEWSKI: The poorest
people who get
health insurance through the
Affordable Care

21:07.699 --> 21:12.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Act, or Obamacare's insurance
exchanges, these
are people that as an individual
can make

21:12.971 --> 21:16.074 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
