year.

21:16.108 --> 21:21.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They are people who are such
low-income that
they need help with the
deductibles and the

21:21.980 --> 21:23.382 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
co-pays.

21:23.415 --> 21:26.385 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And how much
money are we talking
about is involved?

21:26.418 --> 21:27.986 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I have seen $130-some-billion.

21:28.020 --> 21:30.856 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT LASZEWSKI: Yes, it's
about $1,000 per
person.

21:30.889 --> 21:31.857 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A year?

21:31.890 --> 21:33.025 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ROBERT LASZEWSKI: Yes.

21:33.058 --> 21:34.493 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

21:34.526 --> 21:37.896 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROBERT LASZEWSKI: So, it's a
huge amount of
money for that individual.

21:37.929 --> 21:40.799 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's a huge amount of money to
the insurance
company that is providing it,
because the

21:40.832 --> 21:44.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
