this reservoir
of goodwill.

38:04.582 --> 38:07.251 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Think of it like having a bank
account that
you're flush with cash.

38:07.285 --> 38:12.323 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so you spend that money down
and that
goodwill down over the course of
your presidency

38:12.356 --> 38:14.458 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to get things done.

38:14.492 --> 38:16.027 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump is starting in a
very different
place.

38:16.060 --> 38:19.964 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He has got to find a way to fill
that reservoir
because, right now, it's empty.

38:19.997 --> 38:24.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's sitting at anywhere between
40 percent
and 42 percent approval, the
lowest for any

38:24.835 --> 38:30.241 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
president at this point in his
tenure, for
a first-term president in his
tenure.

38:30.274 --> 38:34.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so the question which, Judy,
I feel like
we have been asking since the
day he that

38:34.478 --> 38:38.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
won this election is how does he
fill that
reservoir because, right now, he
hasn't done

38:38.349 --> 38:40.851 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a particularly good job of it.

38:40.885 --> 38:43.921 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Tam, you not
only cover
Washington.

38:43.954 --> 38:45.723 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You cover the American people.

38:45.756 --> 38:47.758 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You hit the road.

38:47.792 --> 38:51.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How do you sense the importance
of this measurement,
this 100 days?

38:51.696 --> 38:56.801 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH, National Public
Radio: It is
an arbitrary measure.

38:56.834 --> 39:04.842 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is based on, you know, the
Roosevelt administration
had -- FDR's administration had
incredible

39:04.875 --> 39:06.610 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
accomplishments.

39:06.644 --> 39:10.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But that was done with Congress,
and a lot
of it didn't originate from the
White House.

39:10.214 --> 39:15.019 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One historian I talked to last
week said that
even Roosevelt wouldn't have
meet the standard.

39:15.052 --> 39:17.855 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And yet every president is held
to this standard.

39:17.888 --> 39:23.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The problem with President Trump
is that he
made big all of these very
promises, and specifically

39:23.227 --> 39:27.531 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
labeled it as his 100-days plan
that he was
campaigning on.

39:27.565 --> 39:33.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That said, as the talk of 100
days heated
up last week, I was chatting
with a Trump

39:33.871 --> 39:39.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
